==English==

{{webster}}
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[instigatus]]'', past participle of ''[[instigare]]'' to instigate; prefix [[in-]] in + [[a]] root akin to {{G.}} ''[[stechen]]'' to prick, {{E.}} [[stick]].

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|instigat|e}}
# To goad or urge forward; to set on; to provoke; to incite; -- used chiefly with reference to evil actions; as to instigate one to a crime.
#:''He hath only instigated his blackest agents to the very extent of their malignity.''  -Bp. Warburton.

===Synonyms===
*[[stimulate]]; [[urge]]; [[spur]]; [[provoke]]; [[tempt]]; [[incite]]; [[impel]]; [[encourage]]; [[animate]].